As Title States.

74in diameter and pitched to 54. It has laminated leading edge protection.

This prop has never flown. It was ordered last spring for my project, used for some test engine runs. but never spun passed 1500rpm. Always stored horizontally in my dry hangar.

This prop is for an O-320 with 3/8 propeller bolts. I will include a bolt set from Saber Mfg (length is set for a 1/2 crush plate and .080 spinner bulkheads)

Asking 500$
